    "## 6. Progressive Unfreezing \u2014 MobileNetV2\n",
    "\n",
    "Progressive unfreezing is an advanced transfer learning technique that gradually \"thaws\" backbone layers from top to bottom over multiple training phases:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Phase 1** \u2014 Train only the classifier head (already done above)\n",
    "2. **Phase 2** \u2014 Unfreeze the last few backbone layers and fine-tune with a reduced learning rate\n",
    "3. **Phase 3** \u2014 Unfreeze more layers, further reduce LR\n",
    "\n",
    "This avoids catastrophic forgetting (destroying pretrained features) while allowing the model to adapt deeper features to the target domain. The lower learning rate for unfrozen layers is critical \u2014 pretrained weights are already close to optimal and only need small adjustments."
   ],
   "id": "921078ef6f35f3f0"
